<br />

<br />
Elemental Draw / Elemental Siphon
<br />
Protection of Calliav
<br />

<br />
--
<br />

<br />
I personally see the spells as being OK (not great, but ok-- the names are cool too).  There are some ideas that I'd really want (like a scaleable DS -- kind of a reverse BoV), but in general they look ok.  I certainly won't complain about being to crit with Bolt of Jerikor for 5720 with a simple ID4 focus.  The increase dmg modifier to the BO line of spells looks nice too (parses will tell).
<br />

<br />
The biggest thing is, if we get any type of really useful utility line of spell it will have to balanced against all the other classes which is not a easy to do.  More often than not we will get a great utility spell that will be eventually be nerfed b/c it makes us too powerful and then the spell just sits at the back of our spellbook.
<br />

<br />
Maybe I'm in the minority, but from an overall DPS standpoint I think mages do quite well.  I parsed at 315 DPS on keeper of the alter with a simple Anger of Druzzil (23% magic) / rock of taelosia, spell haste IV and MS4 pet (with ldon focus).  I find that to be quite acceptable.  (note:  i would like to see an increase in pet DPS though)
<br />

<br />
BTW, this is not a flame nor is this post directed at anyone so don't respond and make it personal.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=653282" target=_blank>Casala</a>
<br />
<a href="http://www.hneguild.com" target=_blank>Heaven and Earth</a>
<br />
Saryrn</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
