				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Thank you Rytan for that update. That is great news if this is only the start and more exciting things are waiting in the wings. With that in mind please for gods opps oow sakes remove the recast time on the mage pet heal spell and up the amount it heals. As it is now the oow heal maybe ok (with no recast time in PoP), it is not near good enough for god, and oow at level 70 will make it a meaningless spell yet again. Please I implore you make it heal for a lot more, and no recast times.
<br />

<br />
Cyricus I agree with you and your suggestions, though raising a shield against say magic in plane of fire would make mage's 100% useless as fire will not land, unless they drop the fire immunity to get magic. If that were the case, it could be interesting to use a fire spell in plane of fire (to give one example). Can't ever have a mob both immune to fire and magic, or we are in the SoV early days of mages contributing no damage as everything bounces, and we sit and do nothing. The beginning of the dark days for mages everywhere. I know you lived through it as I did as well. Original idea for spells and AA's would breath new life into th game, and abot time they did this.
<br />

<br />
As for Lore, a suggestion that we find out that Rallos Zek is behind the mobs in OOW. Say something to the fact that even though the timelines were restored RZ still knows what happened. The chronical complied by Karana was stolen (after all Karana was not in the Plane of Time, and was tasked with chronicalling the event), maybe not stolen but Agnarr passed it to RZ before the players killed him and freed Karana. Perhaps that was the task that Askar was sent on, to retrieve it. After all it was vague where he was sent. As the PoTime happened in the past, the history was written already, so Karana having the records is nothing new, but Agnarr is, and well you get the drift. A way to tie oow into PoP. RZ out for revenge, and he hid that continent (after all he always had maps off all of Norath in his zones). Just one idea to get EQ back on track as far as lore is concerned. FLesh it out, and make it interesting. Maybe add that Karana wrote it all in a code, and RZ doesn't know all that happened and is decyphering it. We kil the OOW boss to recover it, and than Kaarana appears to take it into safe custody. Sounds like something wrothwhile to me. 
<br />

<br />
If Rytan reads this I have one question about customre support. I have a ticket in the Que since Sunday, and it is now Friday, and besides one automated update, a GM posted on it a senior GM needs to look at it. 5 full days a ticket in the que and I have heard nothing personally, and the GM comment, was just that a cooment, and nothing done. I am sure you agree 5 days is way too long for anyone to have to wait for some customer service. At least the new ticket system shows it out there, but beyound that, nothing is done. Also there is no way to email a gm as the option is removed, it says use the ingame petition system. I even called, and the automated message says the same. No way to talk to a person. Sorry but that is not customer service. There shuld be a way to automatically escalate any ticket in the que after no resolution after say 72 to even 96 hours. That way players know something will happen. %Thanks for listening Rytan if you read this.
<br />

<br />
Calebe</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
